node.text: My friend @melissawoodhealth is an absolute superstar, and this new @HarvardHBS case — written by my colleague Eva Ascarza — proves it. So amazing to see Melissa become one of today’s top players in the creator economy and to watch her continue to expand her business (move over, @noahtepperberg — there’s a new star in the family! 😂). Congratulations on all your successes, Melissa — and I can’t wait to welcome you back to campus! 🙌

node.text: Guess who the people at @goldmansachs turned to for their first in-person event at their headquarters in NYC since the pandemic began? 🙋‍♀️😁❤️ I was honored and thrilled to be back in action last week, running a session on sports team ownership using my case on The Milwaukee @bucks and @giannis_an34 Antetokounmpo, alongside Goldman Sachs Private Wealth Management’s brilliant Nicole Pullen Ross (@nicoleprosshu, who heads their Sports and Entertainment Solutions business) and Bucks governor Marc Lasry, who chimed in throughout the session with his unique insights on how they turned around the franchise and what it takes to compete effectively with a small-market team, in front of an in-person and online audience who brought a wealth of experience themselves. I couldn’t have asked for a better first trip out of Boston in nearly one and a half years (!). And I can’t wait for more events to come! #weback #yesiworejordansatgoldman 😉

node.text: I was at it in our Live Online Classroom on the @HarvardHBS campus again yesterday, teaching two cases in the CTAM program for cable television executives. And as tradition goes, I sported a new pair of sneakers. Great people, great discussions, great times. 😁 (Big thanks to the instagram-less Wyatt Cmar for the screenshots and Rohan Kumar for the kicks. 🙏)

node.text: They tell me I can ask NBA superstar @cp3 whatever I want — about the NBA bubble last year, his leadership of the NBPA, their social justice initiatives, his already legendary career, his passion for HBCUs, how to make those impossible shots he showed off last night 🙌, and much, much more — so this promises to be interesting! 😁 Meant for students but really anyone can sign up (link in @cp3’s bio), so feel free to join! Thank you @zoom for making this happen! 🙏

node.text: One moment I’m chilling on the couch on a Sunday evening, and the next I see myself pop up during the @NBA All-Star game... I had absolutely no idea that was going to happen! (Heart rate is still elevated even a day later. 😁) Awesome to be able to give some love to the HBCUs, though, and see our initiative featured so prominently. 😍 Big thanks to @cp3 and his team for the vision and hard work (I see you @goodcarma17), to @nbaontnt for only showing my good sides 😉, to @bobbymetelus and @kev.wolf for capturing the original footage, and to @swengbeg for putting it together. And thanks everyone for all your messages last night — my phone exploded. 🙌

node.text: Congratulations to @HarvardHBS  BEMS program graduates @cp3 and @juliusrandle30 on their 11th (!) and 1st NBA All-Star selections, respectively. Such great accomplishments! I figured it makes for a good excuse to post some throwback photos. 😁 The one with Chris is from one of my last public outings last year, after a Celtics game here in Boston. The one with Julius is right before the multitalented @ciara came flying in — swipe left for that golden oldie. Good times (📸: @evephoto) 😍 Looking forward to the game tonight!

node.text: I finally had a reason to don my familiar black suit again last week, to teach (on campus, for the first time in a year!!!) in the @HarvardHBS live online classroom. 🖤 This was a session in the “Developing Yourself as a Leader” executive education program, in which I taught my case on the legend @dwyanewade. Still far from a normal experience — no one could be there with me in the studio, for instance (and so the action shots are taken from the control room as well; thank you, @agrace4!) — but even then it felt goooood to be back! I feel very lucky we have such amazing resources at HBS. And the fresh sneakers helped, too, of course (big props to @steineey 🙏). 😍

node.text: What started as an experiment with a small group of NBA athletes a little over three years ago (I have the photos to prove it 😊) this week became an enormous undertaking, as we welcomed 75 (!!!) professional athletes into the new edition of our #CrossoverIntoBusiness program, from the NBA, WNBA, NFL, ATP, WTA, MLS, international men’s and women’s soccer, track and field, and a host of other sports. 🙌 Equally special is that more than 200 current students and alumni answered the call to volunteer as their mentors. 💪 We asked each team of mentors to prepare one slide to pitch themselves, and shared two large draft books containing all those slides with the athletes so they could pick their favorites. And then our draft algorithm did its thing, matching athletes to their teams, the outcome of which was announced in one large zoom session. Such a beautiful thing to see the @HarvardHBS community step up in this way, especially during the pandemic! ❤️ Thank you everyone, for showing how special Harvard can be! 🙏🙏🙏 (Oh, while I’m at it — make sure to preorder Crossover champion @chrisbosh’s new book, “Letters to a Young Athlete”! 🔥)
